alert.note: Alert for Franklin; Gulf; Liberty (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Tornado Warning issued September 26 at 8:32AM EDT until September 26 at 9:00AM EDT by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: The National Weather Service in Tallahassee has issued a * Tornado Warning for... Eastern Gulf County in the Panhandle of Florida... South central Liberty County in Big Bend Florida... North central Franklin County in Big Bend Florida... * Until 900 AM EDT. * At 831 AM EDT, a severe thunderstorm capable of producing a tornado was located 15 miles southeast of Wewahitchka, or 18 miles north of Eastpoint, moving northeast at 25 mph. HAZARD...Tornado. SOURCE...Radar indicated rotation. IMPACT...Flying debris will be dangerous to those caught without shelter. Mobile homes will be damaged or destroyed. Damage to roofs, windows, and vehicles will occur. Tree damage is likely. * This tornadic thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of eastern Gulf, south central Liberty and north central Franklin Counties, including the following locations... Twin Pole, Sumatra, and Owens Bridge. TORNADO...RADAR INDICATED MAX HAIL SIZE...<.75 IN
info.instruction: TAKE COVER NOW! Move to a basement or an interior room on the lowest floor of a sturdy building. Avoid windows. If you are outdoors, in a mobile home, or in a vehicle, move to the closest substantial shelter and protect yourself from flying debris.
